title: UVA shooting: Football team's final game of season vs. Virginia Tech canceled
description: The University of Virginia's football team had its second game canceled in wake of a shooting that left three players dead and two wounded.

title: Washington, D.C. man who helped pass criminal code overhaul shot and killed
description: A man who helped usher criminal justice reform through city council in Washington, D.C., was shot and killed in the early morning hours of Nov. 15.

title: Philadelphia receives second bus of migrants from Texas as border security initiative ramps up
description: A second bus carrying illegal immigrants from Texas arrived Monday in Philadelphia, with city officials accusing Gov. Abbott of using migrants as pawns.

title: 'The View' hosts fret over Twitter after Musk reinstates Trump: 'Just leave him out of it'
description: "The View" hosts reacted to the news that former President Trump's Twitter account was reinstated by Elon Musk after he polled users on the site.

title: Gavin Rossdale on Taylor Swift ticket fiasco: 'Everybody wants to crash the servers’
description: Gavin Rossdale chimes in on the Taylor Swift Ticketmaster fiasco, admitting that it's a "super high-class problem." Rossdale is about to go on tour with his band, Bush.

title: Broncos waive veteran running back Melvin Gordon after costly fumble
description: The Denver Broncos waived veteran running back Melvin Gordon III on Monday, one day after a 22-16 overtime loss to the Las Vegas Raiders.

title: Idaho police: Dog found skinned head-to-tail is unrelated to college students' murders
description: A 12-year-old dog was found skinned head-to-tail in Moscow, Idaho, just three weeks before four college students were murdered, but police say the two crimes are unrelated.

title: Idaho murder victim Ethan Chapin remembered as 'one of the most incredible people you will ever know'
description: Friends and family of University of Idaho homicide victim Ethan Chapin on Friday remembered the 20-year-old student and athlete as someone who 'loved life.'

title: California attorney of driver charged in wrong-way crash that injured 25 recruits says client asleep at wheel
description: The attorney of a man accused of intentionally striking LA County recruit officers says her client was asleep at the wheel and the crash was unintentional.

title: Ex-UFC star Cain Velasquez pleads not guilty in attempted murder case
description: Two-time UFC heavyweight champion Cain Velasquez pleaded not guilty in an attempted murder case in which he allegedly shot at a man who is accused of sexually assaulting his son.

title: Caitlyn Jenner blames 'woke' Washington rules for allowing trans runner to dominate female competitors
description: Caitlyn Jenner discussed the latest case of transgender participation in womens sports as a biologically male student dominates female track competitors in Seattle.

title: Florida Keys rescue sees Coast Guard save 22 people, many children, from overloaded sailing vessel
description: Nearly two dozen people were rescued from an overloaded sailing vessel off the coast of the Florida Keys on Monday, according to the Coast Guard.

title: New Mexico State basketball player was 'lured' to campus by four UNM students ahead of fatal shooting: police
description: The New Mexico State Police said Sunday that they believe New Mexico State forward Mike Peake was "lured" on to UNM campus by four students, one of whom was fatally shot by Peake.

title: Jets won't commit to Zach Wilson starting vs. Bears
description: Changing his comments after Sunday's brutal loss to the New England Patriots, New York Jets head coach Robert Saleh didn't commit to Zach Wilson being his starting quarterback Sunday.

title: Todd and Julie Chrisley sentenced to federal prison; reality stars receive combined 19 years behind bars
description: "Chrisley Knows Best" stars Todd and Julie Chrisley received a combined 19 years in federal prison after being found guilty by Georgia judge in tax evasion case.

title: Idaho police's expansion of crime scene could possibly mean attempt to uncover new evidence, official says
description: The chief of the nearby Washington State University Police reacted Monday to new reports surrounding the murder of four University of Idaho students.

title: Bill Maher slams woke college campuses: 'There is a rot, and it comes from academia'
description: Bill Maher slammed the parents of the man at the core of the FTX scandal, noting they come from academia, an American institution he says is rife with political groupthink.
